ðŸ§  How a CTOR Bot Works
A bot is simply a JavaScript function that receives:

the current board state,

the botâ€™s color ("R" or "B"),

the move history,

optional helper functions.

It must return a move:

js
{ row: Number, col: Number }
A minimal bot looks like this:

js
function myBot(board, color) {
  return { row: 0, col: 0 };
}
ðŸ›  How to Write Your Own Bot
1. Create a file named myBot.js
Example:

js
export function myBot(board, color) {
  // Find the first empty cell
  for (let r = 0; r < 8; r++) {
    for (let c = 0; c < 8; c++) {
      if (board[r][c] === ".") {
        return { row: r, col: c };
      }
    }
  }
  return null; // no moves available
}
2. Make sure the function is exported
The platform expects:

Code
export function myBot(...)
3. Save the file as myBot.js
ðŸ§ª How to Test Your Bot on the Platform
Open the CTOR GAME AI vs AI page (GitHub Pages).

Scroll to Upload Custom Bot.

Click Choose File and select your myBot.js.

Your bot will appear in the Available Bots list.

Select it as Bot R or Bot B.

Press Start Match.

Use:

Next Move â€” step-by-step mode

Auto Play â€” continuous mode

Stop â€” pause the match

